Check if all digits of the given integer are even.

Example

For n = 248622, the output should be
solution(n) = true;
For n = 642386, the output should be
solution(n) = false.


My solution:

def solution(n):
    return False if [int(x) for x in str(n) if int(x) % 2 != 0] else True
    
    Pretty straightforward. Iterate through str(n) using list comp and ensure all int values in the string are even.
